2. What are the different types of flows in Power Automate?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
Power Automate supports five main types of flows:

ğŸ”¹ 1. Automated Flow:
ğŸ‘‰ Triggered automatically by specific event or condition.
ğŸ‘‰ For Example, when a new item is added to a SharePoint list, an email is received in Outlook, or a file is created in OneDrive.

ğŸ”¹ 2. Instant Flow (Button Flow):
ğŸ‘‰ Manually triggered by users, typically through a button press. (in Power Apps or the Power Automate mobile app).
ğŸ‘‰ It allows users to start actions on demand, such as sending approvals, sending notifications.

ğŸ”¹ 3. Scheduled Flow:
ğŸ‘‰ Runs on a define schedule â€” (e.g., daily, weekly, hourly) â€” to automate repetitive tasks.
ğŸ‘‰ For Example, Automatically generate and email a report every Monday at 9 AM.

ğŸ”¹ 4. Business Process Flow (BPF):
ğŸ‘‰ Used in Model-Driven Apps to guide users through a multi-step business process.

ğŸ”¹ 5. Desktop Flow (RPA):
ğŸ‘‰ Used for Robotic Process Automation(RPA) to automate manual tasks on desktop (e.g., legacy systems).
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

