ğŸ‘‰ Conditions in Power Automate are used to create logic-based decision branches, 
   â€” meaning the flow can take different actions depending on whether a condition is true or false.

ğŸ”§ Example (Real-time use): 
ğŸ‘‰ In one of my flows, I used a Condition to check if a SharePoint itemâ€™s status is "Pending".
If Approved(true):
ğŸ‘‰ Update the SharePoint item status to "Approved"
ğŸ‘‰ Send an Outlook email to employee with subject: â€œLeave Request Approvedâ€

If Rejected(false):
ğŸ‘‰ Update status to "Rejected"
ğŸ‘‰ Send rejection email to the employee
