6. What is a Scope in Power Automate?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Scope is like a container control in Power Automate that is used to group multiple actions together.
ğŸ‘‰ It helps in organizing flows and especially useful for error handling, debugging, and logical separation of actions.

ğŸ”§ For Example:
ğŸ‘‰ I use Scopes to grouped all the main actions â€” like creating a record, sending an email, and updating SharePoint â€” inside a Scope called â€˜Tryâ€™.
ğŸ‘‰ One key benefit is that I can apply â€˜Configure Run Afterâ€™ logic to an entire Scope.
ğŸ”¹ For example:
â€” I have a â€˜Main Actionsâ€™ scope that performs all business logic
â€” Then a second â€˜Error Handlingâ€™ scope that only runs if the first scope fails
