7. How can you handle errors in Power Automate flows?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰"In Power Automate,
I handle errors using a combination of Configure Run After, Scope actions, and proper error logging.
For example, I usually create separate scopes like Try, Catch, and Finally. 
In the Try scope, I place the main logic of the flow, and
in the Catch scope, I configure it to run only if the Try scope fails using the 'Configure Run After' option.(Has Failed,Is Skipped, Has timeout) 

Inside the Catch scope, I log the error details in SharePoint or Dataverse and send a failure notification email to the support team so they are aware of the issue.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

